<component type="desktop-application">
  <id>io.github.d0ksan8.zen-app-manager</id>
  <name>Zen App Manager</name>
  <summary>Manage your startup applications easily</summary>
  <metadata_license>CC0-1.0</metadata_license>
  <project_license>MIT</project_license>
  <description>
    <p>
      Zen App Manager is a modern, lightweight tool designed to help you manage your startup applications on Linux.
      It provides a simple interface to enable or disable apps that run when your computer starts, helping you improve boot times and system performance.
    </p>
    <p>Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Simple toggle interface to enable/disable startup apps</li>
      <li>Add new applications or custom commands to startup</li>
      <li>Modern, dark-themed UI (AMOLED friendly)</li>
      <li>Lightweight and fast (Built with Rust &amp; Tauri)</li>
      <li>Smart detection of startup entries</li>
      <li>File size and location indicators</li>
    </ul>
  </description>
  <launchable type="desktop-id">io.github.d0ksan8.zen-app-manager.desktop</launchable>
